    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "How long does a pelvic MRI take?",
        "answer": "25–40 minutes depending on contrast use.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Is pelvic MRI painful?",
        "answer": "No. You may feel warmth from the coil; no needles unless contrast is used.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I eat before a pelvic MRI?",
        "answer": "Yes, unless contrast is scheduled—then fast 4 hours.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "When will I get my results?",
        "answer": "Within 24 hours online; printed copy available on request.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Is the scan safe during pregnancy?",
        "answer": "Only in late pregnancy and only if medically essential—consult your doctor.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What is the average cost of an MRI Pelvis scan?",
        "answer": "The **average cost of an MRI pelvis scan** can vary depending on several factors. These include the specific type of **MRI Pelvis** being performed (e.g., with or without contrast, specialized protocols), the complexity of the study, and geographical location.\n\nFor detailed and accurate information on the cost of an **MRI Pelvis** at Cadabams Diagnostics, including any potential insurance coverage questions, please contact our billing department or patient services directly. You can find our contact details on our page. They will be happy to provide you with a cost estimate."
      }
    ],
