    "markdown": "## MRI Pelvis Overview\n\n### Why Cadabams Diagnostics for Your Pelvic MRI\n- \\*\\*3-T MRI machines\\*\\* for razor-sharp images\n- \\*\\*Same-day & next-day\\*\\* appointment slots\n- \\*\\*Female & male technicians\\*\\* on request\n- \\*\\*Online report access\\*\\* within 24 hours\n- \\*\\*Transparent pricing\\*\\*—no hidden fees\n\n## Risks & Limitations of MRI Pelvis\n\n### Contrast-Related Concerns\n- \\*\\*Gadolinium\\*\\* is generally safe; rare risk of nephrogenic systemic fibrosis in severe kidney disease.\n- Allergy screening questionnaire before injection.\n### Claustrophobia & Metal Implants\n- \\*\\*Open-bore MRI\\*\\* option for anxious patients.\n- \\*\\*Absolute contraindications\\*\\*: Pacemaker, cochlear implants, certain aneurysm clips.\n- \\*\\*Tattoos & piercings\\*\\* may heat up—remove jewelry.\n\n## List of Parameters Considered During MRI Pelvis\n\n- \\*\\*Uterus & Ovaries\\*\\*: Size, position, masses, endometrial thickness\n- \\*\\*Prostate & Seminal Vesicles\\*\\*: Volume, lesions, capsule invasion\n- \\*\\*Bladder & Rectum\\*\\*: Wall thickness, diverticula, tumors\n- \\*\\*Lymph Nodes & Vascular Structures\\*\\*: Enlargement, thrombosis, varices\n\n## When to Take Test\n\n\\*\\*Endometriosis Detection\\*\\*\nMRI spots tiny endometrial implants missed on ultrasound.\n\\*\\*Infertility Work-Up\\*\\*\nEvaluates uterine anomalies, tubal patency, and ovarian reserve.\n\\*\\*Prostate Cancer Staging\\*\\*\nDetermines tumor size, spread to seminal vesicles, and lymph-node involvement.\n\\*\\*Pelvic Pain Diagnosis\\*\\*\nIdentifies causes like adenomyosis, abscesses, or hernias.\n\n## Benefits of Taking the Test\n\n- \\*\\*High-resolution Images\\*\\*: 3-T magnet shows 1 mm structures.\n- \\*\\*No Radiation Exposure\\*\\*: Safe for repeated follow-ups.\n- \\*\\*Early Detection & Treatment Planning\\*\\*: Catch cancers before symptoms arise.\n\n## Illnesses Diagnosed with MRI Pelvis\n\n- \\*\\*Gynecological Cancers\\*\\*: Cervical, endometrial, ovarian\n- \\*\\*Prostate Hyperplasia & Cancer\\*\\*: BPH, adenocarcinoma\n- \\*\\*Pelvic Inflammatory Disease\\*\\*: Tubo-ovarian abscess\n- \\*\\*Congenital Anomalies\\*\\*: Bicornuate uterus, imperforate hymen\n\n## Preparing for MRI Pelvis\n\n### Fasting & Medication Guidelines\n- \\*\\*4-hour fast\\*\\* if contrast is planned.\n- Take regular meds with sips of water.\n### Clothing & Personal Items\n- Wear \\*\\*metal-free\\*\\* cotton gown; leave valuables at home.\n### Informing Staff about Implants or Pregnancy\n- Notify us of \\*\\*pregnancy\\*\\* or any \\*\\*implants\\*\\*—we’ll adjust protocols.\n---\n## Pre-requisites\n- \\*\\*Doctor’s Prescription\\*\\*: Upload on our portal or bring a hard copy.\n- \\*\\*Previous Imaging Reports\\*\\*: Bring CDs or films for comparison.\n---\n## Best Time to Take the MRI Pelvis\n### Menstrual Cycle Considerations for Women\nDays \\*\\*5–10\\*\\* of cycle reduce endometrial artifacts.\n### Optimal Scheduling for Prostate Imaging\nBook \\*\\*4–6 weeks after biopsy\\*\\* to minimize hemorrhage interference.\n---\n## Eligibility\n### Who Cannot Undergo MRI\n- Pacemaker, cochlear implants, insulin pumps, or severe claustrophobia without sedation.\n### Pediatric & Geriatric Adaptations\n- \\*\\*Kids\\*\\*: Mild sedation or play therapy.\n- \\*\\*Elderly\\*\\*: Wheelchair-friendly suite, extra cushions.\n---\n## Procedure for Taking a MRI Pelvis\n1. \\*\\*Arrival & Check-In\\*\\*: 15 minutes early for paperwork.\n2. \\*\\*Positioning & Coil Placement\\*\\*: Lie supine; pelvic coil placed over lower abdomen.\n3. \\*\\*Scan Duration & Noise Expectations\\*\\*: 25–40 minutes; loud knocking—earplugs provided.\n---\n## Caution Before Taking the Test\n- \\*\\*Contrast Allergy Screening\\*\\*: Questionnaire + antihistamine on standby.\n- \\*\\*Kidney Function Tests\\*\\*: Creatinine if gadolinium is planned."
